  h2.under Alternative opening
  p Branding is simple. Tell people who you are. Say it a way that people remember.
  p
    a(href="") no name
    |!{' '}is a “low cost, no frills” supermarket brand in Canada.
  p How can they communicate this in a way that people remember?
  p Most discount brands try and persuade with slogans, packaging, and cost-saving ads. But that's hardly “no-frills”.
  p Most brands run cost-saving ads or slap “20% extra free” on their packaging. But that’s hardly “no frills”.
  p So no name went the other way. They stripped away the persuasive layer of a brand. Right down the bare bones.
  p The packaging is plain. The website says “website”. Their sole ad campaign of the last decade saw them matter-of-factly label parts of Toronto’s subway station.
